      <hedline>
        <hl1>Recycling, Our Gift to Tomorrow</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>John Cantilli letter holds that John Tierney's Aug 8 column on economics of recycling is shortsighted</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>John Tierney's discussion of the local economics of recycling is rather shortsighted (Big City column, Aug. 8).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>John Tierney's discussion of the local economics of recycling is rather shortsighted (Big City column, Aug. 8).</p>
        <p>Recycling paper, plastic, glass and metal saves trees, oil and energy derived from combustion of fossil fuels. Combustion causes global warming and acid rain. The benefits of recycling are not only obvious; they are also priceless.</p>
        <p>JOHN CANTILLI  Cranford, N.J., Aug. 8, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
